<Link id="l01544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1544"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1545"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Current sequence of rows being extracted, before being inserted</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1546"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in NewRows.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1547"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::vector&lt;DWARFDebugLine::Row&gt; Seq;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1548"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1549"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &amp;FunctionRanges = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dwarf-linker/parallel/compileunit/#a93cea00bbe10a959098b13fdc7bee00f">getFunctionRanges</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1550"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::optional&lt;AddressRangeValuePair&gt; CurrRange;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1551"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1552"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: This logic is meant to generate exactly the same output as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1553"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Darwin&#39;s classic dsymutil. There is a nicer way to implement this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1554"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// by simply putting all the relocated line info in NewRows and simply</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1555"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// sorting NewRows before passing it to emitLineTableForUnit. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1556"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// should be correct as sequences for a function should stay</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1557"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// together in the sorted output. There are a few corner cases that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1558"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// look suspicious though, and that required to implement the logic</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1559"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// this way. Revisit that once initial validation is finished.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01560" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1560"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1561"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Iterate over the object file line info and extract the sequences</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1562"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that correspond to linked functions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1563"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfdebugline/row">DWARFDebugLine::Row</a> Row : InputLineTable-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfdebugline/linetable/#a08f2df6a1aaacec42c6ded0585a11e4d">Rows</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1564"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Check whether we stepped out of the range. The range is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01565" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1565"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// half-open, but consider accept the end address of the range if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01566" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1566"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// it is marked as end&#95;sequence in the input (because in that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1567"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// case, the relocation offset is accurate and that entry won&#39;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01568" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1568"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// serve as the start of another function).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1569"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!CurrRange || !CurrRange-&gt;Range.contains(Row.Address.Address)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1570"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We just stepped out of a known range. Insert a end&#95;sequence</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1571"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// corresponding to the end of the range.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1572"><span class="doxyHighlight">        uint64&#95;t StopAddress =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1573"><span class="doxyHighlight">            CurrRange ? CurrRange-&gt;Range.end() + CurrRange-&gt;Value : -1ULL;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1574"><span class="doxyHighlight">        CurrRange = FunctionRanges.getRangeThatContains(Row.Address.Address);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1575"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (StopAddress != -1ULL &amp;&amp; !Seq.empty()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1576"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Insert end sequence row with the computed end address, but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1577"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the same line as the previous one.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1578"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NextLine = Seq.back();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1579"><span class="doxyHighlight">          NextLine.Address.Address = StopAddress;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1580"><span class="doxyHighlight">          NextLine.EndSequence = 1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1581"><span class="doxyHighlight">          NextLine.PrologueEnd = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1582"><span class="doxyHighlight">          NextLine.BasicBlock = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1583"><span class="doxyHighlight">          NextLine.EpilogueBegin = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1584"><span class="doxyHighlight">          Seq.push&#95;back(NextLine);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1585"><span class="doxyHighlight">          insertLineSequence(Seq, NewRows);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1586"><span class="doxyHighlight">        &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1587"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1588"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!CurrRange)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1589"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1590"><span class="doxyHighlight">      &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1591"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1592"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Ignore empty sequences.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1593"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Row.EndSequence &amp;&amp; Seq.empty())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1594"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1595"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1596"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Relocate row address and add it to the current sequence.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1597"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Row.Address.Address += CurrRange-&gt;Value;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1598"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Seq.emplace&#95;back(Row);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1599"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1600"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Row.EndSequence)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1601"><span class="doxyHighlight">        insertLineSequence(Seq, NewRows);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1602"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1603"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1604"><span class="doxyHighlight">    OutLineTable.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfdebugline/linetable/#a08f2df6a1aaacec42c6ded0585a11e4d">Rows</a> = std::move(NewRows);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1605"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
